{
  "ADUs": {
    "ADU1": {
      "text": "God is dead, he declared, brutally, in The Gay Science (1882), and we have killed him.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU2": {
      "text": "We have killed him by no longer believing in his existence.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU3": {
      "text": "The disappearance of God from our lives is, after all, not a trivial matter.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU4": {
      "text": "It cannot simply be ignored, because it changes everything.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU5": {
      "text": "The world has now become a different place entirely: without God there is no certainty, no clarity, and no guarantees about anything.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU6": {
      "text": "With our belief in God we have also lost our trust in the world.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU7": {
      "text": "We don’t know what is going on anymore.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU8": {
      "text": "We have lost all direction, all sense of purpose.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU9": {
      "text": "We no longer know why we are here and where we are going.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU10": {
      "text": "We no longer stand firmly on the ground, but find ourselves in free fall.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU11": {
      "text": "Nothing is in the right place anymore, because we have learned that there are no right places for things (or, for that matter, wrong places).",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU12": {
      "text": "We wander “through an infinite nothingness”; we are surrounded by empty space.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU13": {
      "text": "The world has become colder and darker.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU14": {
      "text": "By killing God we have created quite a mess for ourselves.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU15": {
      "text": "There are other, healthier and more forward-looking ways to respond to the godlessness of the universe than by embracing nihilism.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU16": {
      "text": "The death of God signals the ending of something, but every ending is also a beginning, and this particular ending may actually be beneficial to us.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU17": {
      "text": "The death of God, far from making life meaningless, can be understood as the dawn of a new day, as something liberating, bringing with it a new lightness, full of opportunity and expectation.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU18": {
      "text": "From the death of God new values emerge, which need to replace the old ones, values that are not malformed and tainted by religious beliefs and the worship of an entirely fictional One that is complete, unmoving, and eternal.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU19": {
      "text": "The death of God has given us the chance to reinvent ourselves, to truly come to life as a higher form of human.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU20": {
      "text": "God’s death can be our resurrection, but only if we prove ourselves worthy of the great deed, which the killing of God no doubt is, by becoming gods ourselves.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU21": {
      "text": "The superhuman is the meaning of our existence in the sense that we are meant to be more than what we commonly manage to be.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU22": {
      "text": "There is a potential in human existence that we have not yet realized, or have forgotten how to realize.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU23": {
      "text": "The superhuman is what we could be if we changed the way we look at the world and at ourselves.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU24": {
      "text": "For the superhuman to become real, the human in us must be overcome.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU25": {
      "text": "Man is a rope tied between animal and superhuman – a rope over an abyss.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU26": {
      "text": "Our task, our historic mission, is to sacrifice ourselves to the earth and to “build a house for the superhuman”, which is to say, make all necessary preparations for the superhuman’s arrival.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU27": {
      "text": "All gods are dead; now we want the superhuman to live.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU28": {
      "text": "What distinguishes the superhuman from the human is mostly the way they understand life and themselves, as well as their moral outlook.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU29": {
      "text": "Superhuman is what we will become if we manage to discard the whole set of (Christian) values that most of us have been trained to unquestioningly adhere to and that, in Nietzsche’s view, mostly serves to hold us back and prevent us from living life to the full.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU30": {
      "text": "We need to learn how to dance when we approach our goals: dance with light feet over the mud as if it were ice.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU31": {
      "text": "What makes all things fall, he says, is the “spirit of heaviness”, and it is that spirit that we need to kill.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU32": {
      "text": "Real gods, on the other hand, know how to laugh and to dance.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU33": {
      "text": "We should surround ourselves with those things and learn to laugh about ourselves, because “all good things laugh”.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU34": {
      "text": "We tend to see life as a tragedy, and looking at life this way has not been altogether bad for us because it has at least encouraged us to attach some value to life.",
      "label": "premise"
    },
    "ADU35": {
      "text": "However, it is still misguided.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "ADU36": {
      "text": "What we have to realize is that life is in fact a comedy, something to laugh about, something that can only be properly captured by a “gay science”, which encourages us to explore life with a certain amused detachment.",
      "label": "claim"
    }
  },
